# Rocket.new — Platform Overview

## What Rocket Is
Rocket.new is an AI-powered platform that generates full-stack production web apps from natural language, Figma designs, URLs, or file uploads. Users download the source code and work on it locally.

**Core loop**: Describe → Build → Refine → Ship

## Web App Tech Stack (Fixed)
| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js (TypeScript) App Router OR React (JavaScript) Vite |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS — `darkMode: 'class'` always |
| Backend | Supabase — PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + Edge Functions |
| Supabase package | `@supabase/ssr` — NOT deprecated `auth-helpers-nextjs` |
| Deployment | Netlify |

> Next.js projects = TypeScript only. React projects = JavaScript only (standardized Dec 2025).

## What Rocket Generates in the Codebase
- Complete Next.js App Router file structure
- Supabase client files (`lib/supabase/client.ts`, `server.ts`, `middleware.ts`)
- Authentication flows (login, signup, OAuth callback, protected routes)
- Migration SQL in `supabase/migrations/` folder
- Edge Functions in `supabase/functions/` (if requested)
- Stripe checkout and webhook handlers
- Tailwind-styled components

## What Rocket Does NOT Generate (Must Add Manually)
- Input validation (Zod schemas)
- Rate limiting on API routes
- Error monitoring (Sentry, etc.)
- Database indexes (for performance at scale)
- `robots.txt` and `sitemap.xml`
- CSRF protection
- Image domain whitelisting in `next.config.ts`

