## Platform Updates (March 2026 — Latest)

- **One-prompt whole-app engine**: Rocket has significantly redesigned its core — generating complete applications from a single well-structured prompt with better architecture decisions
- **Enterprise and government positioning**: Rocket now targets enterprise/government deployments — expect more security-conscious generated code patterns in newer projects
- **Agent V2**: Improved understanding and more accurate code generation — prompts that worked in 2024 may produce better output now
- **Auto error detection during generation**: Rocket detects and fixes errors during initial build — cleaner starting codebases, but fixes still needed for logic/business issues
- **iOS mobile app**: Build on-the-go — support context: web projects still download/fix the same way
- **Smart suggestions**: Rocket now analyses your project context and suggests what to build next — affects how users work in Rocket alongside Cursor fixes
- **Auto-detects missing dependencies**: Supabase integration automatically adds required packages — reduces "module not found" on initial setup

## Known Production Issues
1. **Multi-language/i18n** — translation contamination. Build in primary language first.
2. **Token burn rate** — complex apps need 5–15M+ tokens. 1M Starter is demo-only.
3. **One bad prompt can break the app** — rollback is the recovery, not more prompts.

